<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,915,1300]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,1239,1264]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">DISCUSSION:</emphasis>
We did not document 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okamoto" authorityYear="1922" box="[680,823,1240,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Eucapnopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[680,823,1240,1263]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Eucapnopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
during our surveys, but the species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Claassen" authorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Eucapnopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Eucapnopsis brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Eroo River (Surenkhorloo 2009).
</paragraph>
